<IN>
BOND MARKET NEWS (BON)
</IN>
<LP>
   CII FINANCIAL Inc., Burbank, Calif., said it filed a
registration statement with the Securities and Exchange
Commission to offer $40 million principal amount of its
convertible subordinated debentures, due 2005. The provider
of workers' compensation insurance said that Kidder, Peabody
&amp; Co., Allen &amp; Co. and Bateman Eichler, Hill Richards Inc.
will lead the underwriters. A CII spokesman said proceeds
will be used to increase capital to write insurance policies
and to fund a proposed insurance-premium finance subsidiary,
and for general corporate purposes.
</LP>
